Task 1: Basic Task

# 1
~$ ls #I see all the files in a recursive list.This means that 'ls' lists information about all the files within the current directory.

#2
~$ pwd #I see '/home/recruit/Downloads', this means 'pwd' writes the full pathname of the current working directory to the standard output.

#3
~/$ mkdir workspace
~/workspace$ cd workspace

#4
~/workspace$ ls #There is no saved files  in the new directory

#5
~/workspace$ touch README.md

#6
~/workspace$ cp README.md ./CHANGELOG.md


Task 2: Absolute and Relative Paths

~$ touch exercise.md
~$ mv exercise.md /tmp/
~$ rm /tmp/exercise.md

Task 3 : cat commands

#1
~$ cat > umuzi.md
~$ cat > recruits.md
~$ cat > cohorts.md

#2
#Fill in all the information in all the three files.

#3
~$ cat umuzi.md recruits.md cohorts.md

#4
~$ cat umuzi.md recruits.md cohorts.md -> summary.md

#5
~$ cat summary.md

  
Task 4: Locate commands

#1
$ locate umuzi

#2
~$ locate umuzi.md > search_results.md
~$ cat search_results.md


Task 5: The locate command cont..

#1
~$ cd Documents
~$ touch pad.md
~$ ls

#2
~$ mv pad.md ~/Documents
~$ cd ~/Desktop
~$ mkdir work

#3
~$ cp pad.md ~/Desktop/work
~$ ls
~$ cd ~/
~$ cd Desktop
~$ cd work
~$ ls
~$ cp pad.md pad_copy.md

#4
~$ locate updatedb

#5
~$ cd -

#6
~$ locate pad_copy.md
~$ ls

Task: 6 Find commands

#1
~$ find ~/ -name *.pdf 

#2
~$ find ~/ -name *.pdf > resultspdf
~$ cat resultspdf

#3
~$ find . type f -newrmt 2020-01-16 -ls # file is modified specifically for the day the code was executed ex:16 January 2020

